%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20has%20pardoned%20a%20convicted%20murderer%20after%20his%20decided%20to%20enlist%20for%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20Vladislav%20Kanyus%20served%20less%20than%20a%20year%20of%20his%2017-year%20sentence%20for%20brutally%20killing%20his%20ex-girlfriend%2C%20Vera%20Pekhteleva%2C%20reports%20suggest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKanyus%20had%20stabbed%20his%20ex-girlfriend%20111%20times%2C%20raped%20and%20tortured%20her%20for%20three-and-a-half%20hours%2C%20for%20breaking%20up%20with%20him.%20He%20then%20strangled%20her%20with%20a%20cable%20iron%2C%20ultimately%20killing%20her%2C%20according%20to%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesun.co.uk%2Fnews%2F24679644%2Fkiller-raped-ex-stabbing-her-111-times-putin-ukraine%2F%C2%A0%C2%A0%5C%22%3E%20The%20Sun%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Hearing%20her%20scream%2C%20neighbours%20called%20the%20police%20seven%20times%2C%20but%20their%20calls%20went%20unanswered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThis%20revelation%20came%20after%20Vera%20Pekhteleva's%20mother%2C%20Oksana%2C%20discovered%20photographs%20of%20Kanyus%20in%20a%20military%20uniform%20holding%20a%20weapon.%20The%20mourning%20mother%20lamented%2C%20%26quot%3BThis%20was%20a%20blow%20at%20me.%20My%20child%20will%20rot%20in%20her%20grave%20and%20I've%20been%20deprived%20of%20everything%20-%20my%20life%2C%20any%20hope.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BI%20don't%20live%2C%20I%20exist.%20This%20simply%20finished%20me%20off%2C%20it%20just%20totally%20finished%20me%20off.%20I%20am%20a%20very%20strong%20person.%20But%20this%20lawlessness%20of%20our%20state%20just%20pushes%20me%20into%20a%20dead%20end.%20I%20don't%20know%20what%20to%20do%20next%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EWomen's%20rights%20activist%20Alyona%20Popova%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20that%20prison%20authorities%20confirmed%20Kanyus'%20transfer%20to%20Rostov%20in%20southern%20Russia%2C%20bordering%20Ukraine.%20She%20shared%20a%20letter%20from%20the%20Russian%20Prosecutor%20General's%20Office%20dated%20November%203%2C%20stating%20that%20Kanyus%20had%20been%20pardoned%2C%20and%20his%20conviction%20was%20expunged%20by%20a%20presidential%20decree%20on%20April%2027.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EOksana%20is%20heartbroken%20and%20blames%20Putin%20for%20pardoning%20her%20daughter's%20killer.%20She%20is%20confused%20by%20the%20decision%20to%20let%20him%20join%20the%20war%20after%20murdering%20her%20daughter%20and%20is%20now%20worried%20for%20her%20own%20safety.%20%E2%80%9CHow%20could%20a%20cruel%20murderer%20be%20given%20a%20weapon%3F%20Why%20is%20he%20sent%20to%20the%20front%20-%20to%20defend%20Russia%3F%20He%20is%20scum.%20He%20is%20not%20a%20human%20being%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3E%26quot%3B%5BThe%20killer%5D%20can%20at%20any%20moment%20kill%20any%20of%20us%2C%20the%20victims%2C%20out%20of%20revenge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EKremlin%20spokesman%20Dmitry%20Peskov%20defended%20the%20policy%2C%20saying%20that%20Russian%20prisoners%20sent%20to%20fight%20in%20Ukraine%20are%20atoning%20for%20their%20crimes%20%26quot%3Bwith%20blood%2C%26quot%3B%20AFP%20reported.%C2%A0%26quot%3BThose%20convicted%2C%20including%20for%20serious%20crimes%2C%20are%20atoning%20with%20blood%20for%20their%20crime%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.themoscowtimes.com%2F2023%2F11%2F10%2Fkremlin-says-convicts-fighting-in-ukraine-atone-for-crimes-with-blood-a83070%5C%22%3EPeskov%20%3C%2Fa%3Etold%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699685940000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2F0qfobac8_russian-man-who-killed-exgirlfriend_625x300_11_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fvladimir-putin-pardons-russian-man-who-stabbed-ex-girlfriend-111-times-as-he-enlists-for-war-4566185%