l%20Protection%20and%20Emergency%20Management%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEarthquakes%20can%20become%20larger%20than%20those%20that%20have%20occurred%20and%20this%20series%20of%20events%20could%20lead%20to%20an%20eruption%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20administration%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Icelandic%20Met%20Office%20(IMO)%20said%20an%20eruption%20could%20take%20place%20%26quot%3Bin%20several%20days%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20village%20of%20Grindavik%2C%20home%20to%20around%204%2C000%20people%2C%20is%20located%20some%20three%20kilometres%20(1.86%20miles)%20southwest%20of%20the%20area%20where%20Friday's%20earthquake%20swarm%20was%20registered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20evacuation%20plans%20in%20place%20in%20case%20of%20an%20eruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAround%201730%20GMT%2C%20two%20strong%20earthquakes%20were%20felt%20as%20far%20away%20as%20the%20capital%20Reykjavik%20some%2040%20kilometres%20away%2C%20and%20along%20much%20of%20the%20country's%20southern%20coast%2C%20rattling%20windows%20and%20household%20objects.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20preliminary%20IMO%20figures%2C%20the%20biggest%20tremor%20had%20a%20magnitude%20of%205.2%2C%20north%20of%20Grindavik.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolice%20closed%20a%20road%20running%20north-south%20to%20Grindavik%20on%20Friday%20after%20it%20was%20damaged%20by%20the%20tremors.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%2024%2C000%20tremors%20have%20been%20registered%20on%20the%20peninsula%20since%20late%20October%2C%20according%20to%20the%20IMO%2C%20with%20%26quot%3Ba%20dense%20swarm%26quot%3B%20of%20nearly%20800%20quakes%20registered%20between%20midnight%20and%201400%20GMT%20Friday.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20IMO%20noted%20an%20accumulation%20of%20magma%20underground%20at%20a%20depth%20of%20about%20five%20kilometres%20(3.1%20miles).%20Should%20it%20start%20moving%20towards%20the%20surface%20it%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20volcanic%20eruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20most%20likely%20scenario%20is%20that%20it%20will%20take%20several%20days%20rather%20than%20hours%20for%20magma%20to%20reach%20the%20surface%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20a%20fissure%20were%20to%20appear%20where%20the%20seismic%20activity%20is%20at%20its%20highest%20now%2C%20lava%20would%20flow%20to%20the%20southeast%20and%20to%20the%20west%2C%20but%20not%20towards%20Grindavik.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20active%20era%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20the%20Department%20of%20Civil%20Protection%20said%20it%20was%20sending%20the%20patrol%20vessel%20Thor%20to%20Grindavik%20%26quot%3Bfor%20security%20purposes%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEmergency%20shelters%20and%20help%20centres%20were%20to%20open%20in%20Grindavik%20later%20Friday%2C%20as%20well%20as%20three%20other%20locations%20in%20southern%20Iceland%2C%20for%20information%20purposes%20and%20to%20assist%20people%20on%20the%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Thursday%2C%20the%20Blue%20Lagoon%2C%20a%20popular%20tourist%20destination%20located%20near%20Grindavik%20famed%20for%20its%20geothermal%20spas%20and%20luxury%20hotels%2C%20closed%20as%20a%20precaution%20following%20another%20earthquake%20swarm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlso%20nearby%20is%20the%20Svartsengi%20geothermal%20plant%2C%20the%20main%20supplier%20of%20electricity%20and%20water%20to%2030%2C000%20residents%20on%20the%20Reykjanes%20peninsula.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20contingency%20plans%20in%20place%20to%20protect%20the%20plant%20and%20its%20workers%20in%20the%20event%20of%20an%20eruption.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%202021%2C%20three%20eruptions%20have%20taken%20place%20on%20the%20Reykjanes%20peninsula%2C%20in%20March%202021%2C%20August%202022%20and%20July%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThose%20three%20were%20located%20far%20from%20any%20infrastructure%20or%20populated%20areas.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIceland%20has%2033%20active%20volcanic%20systems%2C%20the%20highest%20number%20in%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%