%20and%20was%20asexually%20conceived%20was%20just%20born%20at%20a%20Chicago-area%20zoo%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20epaulette%20shark%20in%20the%20wild%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654ed49bb788914e55547f50%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221414%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20epaulette%20shark%20in%20the%20wild%3Cp%3EHal%20Beral%20%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EA%20Chicago-area%20zoo%20recently%20welcomed%20a%20new%20epaulette%20shark%20pup.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20sharks%20are%20known%20for%20%26quot%3Bwalking%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20large%2C%20round%20spots%20behind%20their%20pectoral%20fins.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20pup%20is%20the%20second%20known%20case%20of%20an%20asexual%20epaulette%20reproduction%20in%20captivity.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fshark-attacks-what-are-odds-of-getting-bitten-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshark%3C%2Fa%3E%20pup%20is%20always%20cause%20for%20celebration%20at%20the%20Brookfield%20Zoo%2C%20but%20the%20birth%20of%20an%20epaulette%20shark%20has%20zookeepers%20especially%20excited%20due%20to%20its%20unusual%20conception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20zoo%2C%20located%20just%20outside%20of%20Chicago%2C%20welcomed%20the%20pup%20on%20August%2023%20%E2%80%94%20but%20her%20mother%20had%20not%20been%20in%20contact%20with%20a%20male%20shark%20since%202019%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fczs.org%2FEpaulette-Shark-Hatches-at-Brookfield-Zoo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epress%20release%20from%20the%20zoo%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20at%20about%20two%20months%20old%2C%20the%20pup%20is%20small%2C%20between%20five%20and%20six%20inches%20long%2C%20said%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEpaulette%20sharks%2C%20which%20can%20reach%20up%20to%203%20feet%20long%20at%20maturity%2C%20are%20easily%20identified%20by%20the%20large%20spots%20behind%20their%20pectoral%20fins.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20they're%20also%20known%20for%20a%20strange%20reason%20%E2%80%94%20being%20able%20to%20%26quot%3Bwalk%26quot%3B%20using%20its%20fins%20both%20on%20land%20and%20in%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUsing%20this%20skill%2C%20the%20sharks%20can%20survive%20harsher%20environments%20and%20move%20between%20tide%20pools%20to%20find%20more%20food%20and%20oxygenated%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20birth%20of%20the%20pup%20in%20Brookfield%20marks%20the%20second%20known%20asexual%20birth%20of%20an%20epaulette%20shark%20in%20an%20accredited%20zoo%20or%20aquarium%2C%20per%20the%20release.%20The%20first%20was%20born%20at%20the%20New%20England%20Aquarium.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20sharks%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-say-they-have-induced-virgin-births-in-fruit-flies-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Easexually%20reproduce%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20process%20is%20called%20automictic%20parthenogenesis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESharks%20producing%20eggs%20usually%20make%20one%20egg%20and%20three%20%26quot%3Bpolar%20bodies%2C%26quot%3B%20shark%20researcher%20Kevin%20Feldheim%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fbaby-shark-asexual-reproduction%2Fa-59055053%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDeutsche%20Welle%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20German%20media%20outlet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20normally%20the%20female%20shark%20reabsorbs%20the%20polar%20bodies%2C%20sometimes%20one%20of%20them%20has%20the%20same%20amount%20of%20genetic%20material%20as%20the%20egg%20and%20fertilizes%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20process%20could%20be%20triggered%20by%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20male%20partner%20in%20sharks%2C%20but%20there%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-sex-exists-2016-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Escientists%20don't%20understand%20about%20the%20process%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20don't%20know%20how%20common%20it%20is%20and%20the%20handful%20of%20cases%20we%20have%20seen%20have%20mostly%20taken%20place%20in%20an%20aquarium%20setting%2C%26quot%3B%20Feldheim%20told%20DW.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pup%20at%20the%20zoo%2C%20housed%20in%20the%20Living%20Coast%20habitat%2C%20continues%20to%20thrive%2C%20per%20the%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpecialists%20at%20the%20zoo%20said%20they%20received%20help%20from%20their%20peers%20at%20the%20New%20England%20Aquarium%2C%20since%20pups%20produced%20parthenogenetically%20may%20be%20more%20delicate%20than%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20happy%20to%20report%20that%20our%20epaulette%20pup%20has%20been%20eating%20well%20on%20her%20diet%20of%20finely%20chopped%20capelin%2C%20minced%20squid%20tentacles%2C%20and%20other%20finely%20chopped%20seafood%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20lead%20animal%20care%20specialist%20Mike%20Masellis%2C%20per%20the%20release.%20%26quot%3BWe%20are%20looking%20forward%20to%20guests%20being%20able%20to%20see%20the%20pup.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepaulette-shark-pup-walk-born-chicago-zoo-asexual-reproduction-egg-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699671225000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F654ed4c83cc84b4dfa009bfb%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepaulette-shark-pup-walk-born-chicago-zoo-asexual-reproduction-egg-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20zoo%2C%20located%20just%20outside%20of%20Chicago%2C%20welcomed%20the%20pup%20on%20August%2023%20%E2%80%94%20but%20her%20mother%20had%20not%20been%20in%20contact%20with%20a%20male%20shark%20since%202019.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Sebastian%20Cahill)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A46%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fepaulette-shark-pup-walk-born-chicago-zoo-asexual-reproduction-egg-20