d%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOperation%20Romeo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DHXRu_RB307I%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EOperation%20Chabutra%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20discourage%20young%20individuals%20from%20gathering%20at%20chabutras%20and%20engaging%20in%20allegedly%20harmful%20activities.%20This%20practice%20was%20primarily%20aimed%20at%20raising%20awareness%20about%20the%20dangers%20of%20underage%20reckless%20bike%20riding%2C%20encouraging%20youngsters%20to%20use%20their%20time%20wisely%20and%20discouraging%20unnecessary%20late-night%20roaming%20that%20the%20police%20believed%20could%20potentially%20contribute%20to%20criminal%20activities.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20a%20chabutra%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChabutra%20is%20a%20colloquial%20term%20used%20in%20Hyderabad%20that%20refers%20to%20a%20raised%20platform%20or%20a%20pavement%20area%20typically%20found%20outside%20houses%20in%20residential%20areas.%20These%20structures%20often%20serve%20as%20community%20spaces%20for%20neighbours%20and%20residents%20to%20congregate%2C%20relax%2C%20or%20engage%20in%20conversations.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorically%2C%20chabutras%20have%20played%20an%20integral%20part%20in%20the%20city%E2%80%99s%20design%2C%20and%20cultural%20fabric%20and%20in%20fostering%20a%20sense%20of%20community%20and%20social%20interaction.%20The%20concept%20of%20a%20chabutra%20draws%20its%20inspiration%20from%20the%20traditional%20village%20settings%20in%20India%20where%20community%20members%20and%20elders%20would%20gather%20beneath%20a%20grand%20tree%20to%20engage%20in%20conversations%20and%20deliberate%20on%20matters%20concerning%20families%20and%20society.%20In%20many%20Indian%20villages%2C%20this%20platform%20also%20served%20as%20the%20assembly%20ground%20for%20the%20local%20panchayat%20to%20conduct%20their%20meetings.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20common%20practice%20in%20India%20to%20have%20small%20indoor%20and%20outdoor%20platforms%20within%20neighbourhoods%20where%20people%20sit%20and%20converse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOver%20time%20this%20concept%20transformed.%20What%20was%20once%20a%20symbol%20of%20community%20bonding%20started%20to%20be%20associated%20with%20gatherings%20of%20youngsters%2C%20especially%20late%20in%20the%20night.%20These%20gatherings%20often%20involved%20socialising%2C%20chatting%2C%20and%20sometimes%20activities%20that%20raised%20concerns%2C%20including%20fights.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20are%20chabutras%20targeted%20by%20the%20police%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20police%20have%20been%20focusing%20their%20attention%20on%20chabutras%20due%20to%20a%20series%20of%20incidents%20in%20which%20conflicts%20between%20two%20groups%20or%20even%20disputes%20among%20friends%20escalated%20to%20tragic%20outcomes%2C%20including%20loss%20of%20life.%20These%20unfortunate%20incidents%20have%20raised%20concerns%20within%20the%20police%20force%20about%20night-time%20gatherings%20in%20the%20old%20city%20areas.%20Information%20provided%20by%20local%20media%20and%20police%20informants%20suggests%20a%20correlation%20between%20these%20gatherings%20and%20the%20occurrence%20of%20violent%20incidents.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%2C%20the%20police%20say%20they%20are%20laying%20more%20emphasis%20on%20ensuring%20that%20young%20individuals%20do%20not%20congregate%20in%20localities%20post-midnight.%20This%20%E2%80%9Cproactive%20approach%E2%80%9D%2C%20they%20say%2C%20aims%20to%20prevent%20confrontations%20and%20altercations%2C%20reduce%20the%20likelihood%20of%20violence%20and%20ultimately%20preserve%20public%20safety.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20police%E2%80%99s%20assumption%20that%20these%20gatherings%20could%20potentially%20lead%20to%20conflicts%20or%20illicit%20activities%20raises%20important%20questions.%20Indeed%2C%20there%20are%20instances%20of%20such%20gatherings%20causing%20disturbances%20to%20residents%20and%20also%20serving%20as%20locations%20for%20criminal%20activities.%20It%E2%80%99s%20crucial%20to%20recognise%20that%20within%20neighbourhoods%2C%20there%20are%20designated%20spots%2C%20often%20in%20alleyways%20or%20side%20streets%2C%20frequented%20by%20known%20troublemakers%20or%20individuals%20with%20criminal%20backgrounds.%20However%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20distinguish%20between%20these%20specific%20individuals%20and%20the%20broader%20community.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECan%20young%20people%20be%20prohibited%20from%20gathering%20with%20friends%3F%20Is%20it%20justifiable%20to%20curtail%20their%20freedom%20of%20peaceful%20assembly%20based%20on%20a%20few%20reported%20instances%20of%20crime%20in%20the%20old%20city%3F%20Does%20the%20law%20permit%20the%20detention%20and%20harassment%20of%20youth%2C%20simply%20for%20sitting%20outside%20their%20residences%3F%20These%20are%20critical%20questions%20that%20warrant%20thoughtful%20examination%20and%20consideration.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%E2%80%99s%20a%20positive%20aspect%20to%20chabutras%20that%20merits%20consideration.%20It%20has%20been%20observed%20that%20when%20residents%2C%20including%20youngsters%2C%20gather%20in%20their%20localities%2C%20it%20serves%20as%20a%20deterrent%20to%20crime%20and%20criminal%20activities.%20The%20presence%20of%20community%20members%20can%20discourage%20outsiders%20from%20attempting%20criminal%20acts%2C%20as%20they%20would%20be%20less%20likely%20to%20go%20unnoticed%20or%20unchallenged.%20This%20highlights%20the%20potential%20for%20chabutras%20to%20provide%20a%20space%20for%20social%20interaction%20%3Cem%3Eand%3C%2Fem%3E%20enhance%20security%20and%20cohesion%20in%20the%20neighbourhood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETherefore%20a%20nuanced%20approach%20that%20addresses%20the%20concerns%20posed%20by%20gatherings%20that%20lead%20to%20disturbances%20and%20criminal%20behaviour%20while%20preserving%20the%20valuable%20role%20they%20can%20play%20in%20maintaining%20a%20safe%20and%20connected%20neighbourhood%20environment%20is%20necessary.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EPolice%20harassment%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20underlying%20motivation%20behind%20police%20operations%20in%20specific%20localities%20is%20complex%20and%20often%20influenced%20by%20various%20societal%20factors%2C%20including%20caste%2C%20class%2C%20and%20religious%20biases.%20To%20comprehend%20this%20intention%2C%20one%20must%20acknowledge%20the%20existing%20societal%20biases%20which%20shape%20the%20attitudes%20of%20government%20agencies%2C%20particularly%20the%20police.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHistorically%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20tendency%20to%20stereotype%20certain%20communities%20and%20areas%2C%20which%20subsequently%20impacts%20the%20orientation%20of%20law%20enforcement%20personnel.%20In%20the%20case%20of%20Hyderabad%E2%80%99s%20old%20city%2C%20it%20has%20often%20been%20portrayed%20as%20an%20area%20with%20potential%20criminal%20elements%2C%20extremists%2C%20and%20terrorists.%20The%20Muslim%20community%20which%20resides%20there%20has%20frequently%20faced%20police%20harassment%2C%20before%20and%20after%20the%20formation%20of%20Telangana.%20Muslim%20youth%20have%20been%20disproportionately%20targeted%20and%20detained%20in%20alleged%20terrorism%20cases%2C%20subjecting%20them%20to%20years%20of%20harassment%2C%20particularly%20following%20the%20Babri%20Masjid%20demolition.%20This%20biased%20perception%20is%20not%20accidental%3B%20rather%2C%20it%20is%20a%20deliberate%20part%20of%20the%20training%20and%20conditioning%20of%20law%20enforcement%20agencies.%20Muslims%20are%20often%20unfairly%20portrayed%20as%20radicalised%20and%20potential%20extremists%20or%20terrorists%2C%20contributing%20to%20a%20global%20narrative%20that%20emerged%20post-9%2F11%2C%20when%20international%20agencies%20began%20associating%20terrorism%20with%20the%20Muslim%20community.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20biases%20against%20Muslims%2C%20caste%20and%20class%20factors%20also%20influence%20the%20mindset%20of%20bureaucrats%20and%20law%20enforcement%20officers.%20There%20is%20a%20perception%20that%20individuals%20from%20backward%20communities%20with%20lower%20socioeconomic%20backgrounds%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20engage%20in%20criminal%20activities.%20This%20perception%20leads%20to%20the%20targeting%20of%20poor%20and%20vulnerable%20localities%20through%20measures%20such%20as%20cordon%20and%20search%20operations%20and%20%E2%80%98Mission%20Chabutra%E2%80%99.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConversely%2C%20affluent%20and%20educated%20neighbourhoods%20often%20escape%20similar%20scrutiny.%20This%20imbalance%20in%20police%20operations%20reflects%20a%20broader%20societal%20bias%2C%20where%20individuals%20from%20disadvantaged%20backgrounds%20are%20disproportionately%20targeted%2C%20while%20those%20from%20privileged%20backgrounds%20enjoy%20relative%20impunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOperation%20Chabutra%20has%20been%20portrayed%20in%20a%20positive%20light%20by%20the%20police%20with%20the%20help%20of%20local%20media.%20But%20of%20late%2C%20there%20has%20been%20a%20surge%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DjUat6S25AzY%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Evideos%20showing%20police%20using%20violent%20force%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20youngsters%2C%20including%20instances%20of%20the%20police%20continuously%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FNewsMeter_In%2Fstatus%2F1715981167537930405%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehitting%20teenagers%20with%20%3Cem%3Elathis%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20This%20escalation%20of%20violence%20on%20a%20large%20scale%20across%20an%20entire%20community%20of%20people%20is%20a%20dangerous%20trend%20emerging%20out%20of%20Hyderabad.%20While%20the%20local%20population%20initially%20supported%20a%20non-violent%20way%20of%20policing%20youth%2C%20they%20are%20increasingly%20concerned%20about%20this%20escalation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20tragedy%20of%20this%20exercise%20is%20that%20instead%20of%20following%20the%20rule%20of%20law%2C%20the%20police%20have%20become%20the%20lawmakers%20in%20Hyderabad.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3ES.Q.%20Masood%20is%20a%20social%20activist%20from%20Hyderabad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699612203000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09165426%2FF9yZn8Ka0AEtKGZ.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fin-hyderabad-policing-of-teens-under-operation-chabutra-is-turning-violent%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20police%20have%20long%20seen%20the%20chabutras%20in%20Old%20City%2C%20a%20place%20for%20social%20gathering%2C%20as%20locations%20for%20youngsters%20to%20indulge%20in%20illegal%20activities%20late%20at%20night.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A7%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Fin-hyderabad-policing-of-teens-under-operation-chabutra-is-turning-violent%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Body%20of%20British%20man%20who%20got%20lost%20on%20hike%20in%20Jamaica%20is%20found%20after%20huge%20search%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699612200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-robert-dyer-jamaica_6355054.jpg%3F20231110134514%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbody-of-british-man-who-got-lost-on-hike-in-jamaica-is-found-after-huge-search-13004660%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20British%20man%20who%20went%20missing%20while%20visiting%20Jamaica%20has%20been%20found%20dead.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbody-of-british-man-who-got-lost-on-hike-in-jamaica-is-found-after-huge-search-13004660%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbody-of-british-man-who-got-lost-on-hike-in-jamaica-is-found-after-huge-search-13004660%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbody-of-british-man-who-got-lost-on-hike-in-jamaica-is-found-after-huge-search-13004660%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20Curious%20Case%20of%20Supreme%20Court's%20Denial%20of%20Bail%20to%20Manish%20Sisodia%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F10151751%2FFnEB_zZaEAAAcQ4.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20days%20of%20prohibition%20in%20the%20US%2C%20the%20bootlegging%20mafia%20generated%20huge%20amounts%20of%20money%20in%20cash.%20The%20acquisition%20of%20cash%20had%20to%20be%20legitimised%20and%20the%20mafia%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20of%20setting%20up%20laundromats%20or%20laundries%2C%20where%20customers%20normally%20pay%20their%20dues%20in%20cash.%20This%20financial%20innovation%20to%20whitewash%20money%20from%20illicit%20trade%20into%20legitimate%20business%20proceeds%20was%20the%20origin%20of%20the%20phrase%20%E2%80%9Cmoney%20laundering%E2%80%9D.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20a%20truth%20universally%20acknowledged%20that%20illicit%20trades%20generate%20large%20amounts%20of%20cash%20and%20one%20of%20the%20ways%20of%20curbing%20illicit%20trade%20is%20to%20curb%20the%20outflow%20and%20utility%20of%20cash%20proceeds.%20The%20process%20of%20money%20laundering%20typically%20involves%20the%20principles%20of%20placement%2C%20layering%20and%20integration.%20Especially%20the%20illicit%20trade%20in%20arms%20and%20drugs%20%E2%80%93%20which%20generates%20huge%20cash%20profits%20%E2%80%93%20was%20sought%20to%20be%20curbed%20on%20an%20international%20scale%20with%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20Financial%20Action%20Task%20Force%20in%201989.%20In%201990%2C%20the%20Political%20Declaration%20and%20Global%20Programme%20of%20Action%20was%20adopted%20and%20in%201998%2C%20the%20Political%20Declaration%20and%20Action%20Plan%20against%20Money%20Laundering%20was%20adopted.%20Following%20the%20adoption%20of%20these%20instruments%2C%20India%20enacted%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%20in%202002.%20Implementation%20of%20the%20Act%20was%20left%20to%20the%20domain%20of%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%2C%20a%20division%20of%20the%20finance%20ministry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20far%20from%20confining%20itself%20to%20the%20laundering%20of%20drugs%20and%20arms%20money%2C%20the%20Indian%20government%20ended%20up%20diluting%20the%20focus%20of%20the%20Act%20by%20including%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20unconnected%20ordinary%20offences%20in%20the%20schedule%20to%20the%20PMLA%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpredicate%20offences%E2%80%9D.%20Crimes%20under%20the%20Copyright%20Act%2C%20pollution%20Acts%20and%20a%20whole%20host%20of%20economic%20offences%20including%20bribery%2C%20were%20jostled%20into%20an%20overbroad%20schedule.%20If%20money%20was%20earned%20from%20any%20of%20these%20offences%20and%20then%20sought%20to%20be%20legitimised%20by%20investing%20its%20proceeds%20in%20the%20creation%20of%20assets%2C%20those%20assets%20were%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98proceeds%20of%20crime%E2%80%99.%20The%20PMLA%20allowed%20the%20state%20to%20seize%20to%20punish%20those%20who%20sought%20to%20launder%20the%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrdinarily%2C%20the%20investigation%20of%20most%20crimes%20is%20done%20by%20the%20State%20Police%20Department%20as%20law%20and%20order%20is%20a%20state%20subject.%20State%20governments%20effectively%20decided%20which%20crimes%20were%20investigated%20and%20which%20were%20neglected.%20The%20Union%20government%20used%20to%20interfere%20in%20criminal%20investigations%20through%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20(CBI).%20However%2C%20the%20CBI%20legislation%20required%20the%20consent%20of%20the%20state%20to%20operate%20within%20its%20territory.%20When%20faced%20with%20overzealous%20central%20investigations%2C%20many%20states%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ftelangana-government-withdraws-general-consent-to-cbi%5C%22%3Erefused%20permission%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20CBI%20to%20operate%20within%20their%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Investigatorial%E2%80%99%20vengeance%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ED%2C%20however%2C%20has%20no%20such%20limitation.%20And%20in%20the%20past%20few%20years%2C%20particularly%20under%20the%20NDA%20government%2C%20it%20has%20become%20an%20institution%20of%20what%20one%20might%20term%2C%20investigatorial%20vengeance%20against%20politicians%20of%20the%20opposition%20parties%20and%20opposition-ruled%20states.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20ED%20recently%20summoned%20Rajasthan%20chief%20minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot%E2%80%99s%20son%20to%20Delhi%20and%20conducted%20searches%20at%20the%20premises%20of%20Chhattisgarh%20chief%20minister%20Bhupesh%20Baghel%E2%80%99s%20political%20adviser.%20In%20short%2C%20electoral%20deficiencies%20were%20remedied%20and%20electoral%20dominance%20was%20achieved%20by%20generous%20resort%20to%20the%20ED.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20Opposition%20politicians%20approached%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20earlier%20this%20year%20against%20the%20misuse%20of%20the%20ED.%20The%20court%2C%20however%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fguidelines-exclusively-for-politicians-sc-turns-down-opposition-petition-on-agency-misuse%5C%22%3Erefused%20to%20entertain%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20petition%20and%20allowed%20the%20petition%20to%20be%20withdrawn%20while%20observing%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%20%E2%80%9CCome%20back%20with%20a%20concrete%20case%2C%20where%20there%20has%20been%20a%20specific%20instance%20or%20instances%20of%20the%20agencies%20being%20used%20to%20selectively%20target%20leaders.%20On%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20law%20that%20we%20have%20laid%20down%2C%20we%20can%20evolve%20general%20principles%20with%20respect%20to%20the%20facts%20of%20the%20case.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20case%20came%20squarely%20before%20the%20court%20in%20Manish%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20bail%20application%20and%20in%20the%20opinion%20of%20this%20author%2C%20the%20judgment%20has%20failed%20the%20standards%20of%20fairness%20to%20which%20every%20accused%20is%20entitled%20and%20sets%20a%20dangerous%20prosecution-friendly%20precedent%20which%20may%20later%20come%20to%20haunt%20those%20who%20are%20in%20power%20today%20but%20may%20not%20be%20in%20the%20same%20position%20tomorrow.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fmanish-sisodia-bail-sc-denial-questions%5C%22%3ENo%20Bail%20to%20Sisodia%3A%20SC%20Ignored%20Basic%20Principles%2C%20Questions%20of%20Targeted%20Political%20Persecution%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhere%20are%20the%20%E2%80%9Cproceeds%20of%20crime%E2%80%9D%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBriefly%20stated%2C%20the%20prosecution%20case%20is%20that%20the%20liquor%20policy%20in%20Delhi%20was%20changed%20to%20give%20wholesale%20distributors%2012%25%20commission%20instead%20of%205%25%20and%20the%20estimated%20difference%20earned%20by%20the%20wholesalers%20was%20to%20the%20order%20of%20Rs%20585%20crore.%20About%20Rs%20100%20crore%20of%20this%20extra%20profit%20has%20been%20alleged%20to%20have%20been%20utilised%20to%20support%20the%20AAP%20campaign%20in%20the%20Goa%20elections.%20There%20appears%20to%20be%20no%20particular%2C%20specific%20money%20which%20is%20directly%20involved%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20Manish%20Sisodia%20or%20under%20his%20direct%20control.%20There%20are%20thus%20no%20directly%20displayable%20%E2%80%9Cproceeds%20of%20crime.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20be%20remembered%20that%20bribery%20is%20an%20offence%20under%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%2C%201988%20and%20is%20a%20predicate%20offence%20under%20the%20PMLA.%20However%2C%20not%20every%20case%20of%20bribery%20is%20a%20case%20of%20money%20laundering%20%E2%80%93%20unless%20and%20until%20the%20money%20generated%20from%20the%20offence%20of%20bribery%20is%20sought%20to%20be%20converted%20into%20assets%20which%20could%20be%20termed%20as%20%E2%80%9CProceeds%20of%20Crime%E2%80%9D.%20In%20the%20absence%20of%20such%20demonstrable%20proceeds%2C%20there%20would%20be%20no%20case%20of%20money%20laundering%20established%20over%20which%20the%20ED%20would%20have%20jurisdiction.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SC%20itself%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F14485072%2F%5C%22%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20vs%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20matter%3Cb%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fb%3Eillustrated%20how%20every%20commodity%20involved%20in%20a%20crime%20does%20not%20turn%20into%20proceeds%20of%20crime.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20vehicle%20used%20in%20the%20commission%20of%20a%20scheduled%20offence%20may%20be%20attached%20as%20property%20in%20the%20concerned%20case%20(crime)%20but%20it%20may%20still%20not%20be%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20%E2%80%9Cproceeds%20of%20crime%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20PMLA.%20%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20these%20circumstances%2C%20it%20does%20reasonably%20appear%20that%20the%20ED%20was%20on%20a%20roving%20and%20fishing%20expedition%20to%20somehow%20connect%20the%20minister%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20liquor%20policy%20with%20the%20crime%20of%20money%20laundering%20and%20to%20possibly%20fix%20others%20higher%20up%20in%20the%20ministerial%20chain%20with%20the%20same%20offence.%20Two%20things%20need%20to%20be%20emphasised%20%E2%80%93%20the%20change%20in%20liquor%20policy%20was%20not%20the%20act%20of%20Sisodia%20alone.%20It%20was%20in%20fact%2C%20endorsed%20by%20a%20cabinet%20decision.%20The%20court%2C%20while%20dealing%20with%20the%20question%20of%20bail%2C%20has%20specifically%20kept%20aside%20the%20question%20of%20whether%20a%20cabinet%20decision%20can%20be%20made%20the%20subject%20matter%20of%20a%20criminal%20prosecution.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20has%20got%20over%20the%20inconvenient%20fact%20that%20there%20currently%20exists%20no%20proven%20money%20trail%20directly%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20Sisodia%20by%20saying%20that%20even%20if%20money%20was%20spent%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20in%20Goa%2C%20he%20exercised%20%E2%80%9Cpossessory%20domain%E2%80%9D%20over%20the%20money%20spent.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20real%20problem%20with%20any%20case%20being%20filed%20by%20the%20ED%20is%20the%20extreme%20difficulty%20in%20securing%20bail.%20Section%2045%20of%20the%20PMLA%20requires%20that%20the%20court%20should%20be%20satisfied%20that%20the%20person%20is%20not%20guilty%20and%20is%20not%20likely%20to%20repeat%20the%20offence.%20Similar%20provisions%20in%20other%20Acts%20have%20been%20interpreted%20by%20the%20court%20to%20make%20the%20grant%20of%20bail%20almost%20impossible%20without%20concluding%20a%20full%20trial.%20It%20is%20also%20pertinent%20to%20state%20that%20very%20rarely%20has%20a%20PMLA%20case%20gone%20to%20trial%20and%20been%20concluded%20in%20a%20reasonable%20amount%20of%20time%2C%20thus%20when%20a%20man%20is%20arrested%20under%20the%20PMLA%20and%20no%20speedy%20trial%20is%20available%20and%20no%20bail%20pending%20trial%20is%20granted%2C%20the%20process%20itself%20is%20the%20punishment.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png-300x150.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png-1024x512.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png-800x400.png%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-670931%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India.%20Photo%3A%20Pinakpani%2FWikimedia%20Commons.%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ESelective%20application%20of%20harsh%20laws%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Sisodia%20judgment%20is%20a%20rare%20lengthy%20judgment%20of%2041%20pages%20which%20denies%20bail%20to%20an%20accused.%20The%20only%20clear%20charge%20that%20the%20court%20has%20relied%20upon%20is%20a%20charge%20of%20causing%20loss%20to%20the%20public%20exchequer.%20Absent%20any%20element%20of%20personal%20aggrandisement%20or%20creation%20of%20proceeds%20of%20crime%2C%20the%20PMLA%20case%20should%20not%20have%20been%20allowed%20to%20continue.%20Instead%2C%20the%20court%20has%20given%20the%20prosecution%20a%20further%20chance%20to%20prove%20its%20case%20and%20allowed%20Sisodia%20an%20opportunity%20to%20apply%20again%20for%20bail%20if%20the%20trial%20moves%20at%20a%20snail%E2%80%99s%20pace%20over%20the%20next%20three%20months.%20This%20judgment%20will%20have%20a%20precedential%20value%20that%20will%20bind%20all%20courts%20in%20India.%20The%20surprisingly%20thin%20logic%20of%20this%20judgment%20will%20end%20up%20denying%20the%20liberty%20of%20a%20lot%20of%20citizens%20other%20than%20Manish%20Sisodia%20who%20have%20also%20been%20caught%20in%20the%20Kafkaesque%20world%20of%20the%20PMLA.%20While%20hard%20cases%20are%20known%20to%20make%20bad%20law%2C%20Sisodia%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20that%20of%20a%20bad%20law%2C%20being%20made%20harder%20by%20a%20harsher%20interpretation%20of%20harsh%20legislation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESomeone%20has%20rightly%20said%20that%20the%20essence%20of%20tyranny%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20a%20harsh%20law%20and%20use%20it%20selectively%20against%20your%20opponents.%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20courts%20fail%20to%20see%20through%20this%20game%2C%20they%20fail%20to%20perform%20their%20constitutional%20duty%20to%20protect%20the%20lives%20and%20liberties%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20citizens.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699610101000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F10151751%2FFnEB_zZaEAAAcQ4.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcurious-case-denial-bail-manish-sisodia-supreme-court%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20rightly%20said%20that%20the%20essence%20of%20tyranny%20is%20the%20ability%20to%20make%20a%20harsh%20law%20and%20use%20it%20selectively%20against%20your%20opponents.%20Our%20courts%20must%20not%20fail%20to%20see%20through%20this%20game.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A62%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fcurious-case-denial-bail-manish-sisodia-supreme-court%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'I%20don't%20want%20to%20go%20from%20one%20war%20to%20another'%3A%20Ukrainians%20in%20Gaza%20await%20evacuation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1699608540000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-rafah-border-gaza-israel-hamas-war_6354650.jpg%3F20231110072546%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fukrainians-await-gaza-evacuation-i-dont-want-to-go-from-one-war-to-another-13004618%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Dozens%20of%20Ukrainians%20have%20been%20evacuated%20from%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20according%20to%20President%20Volodymyr%20Zelenskyy%2C%20as%20Israel%20remains%20vague%20over%20reports%20of%20pauses%20in%20fighting